==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pilfer
<hw>Pil"fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pilfered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pilfering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pelfrer</ets>. See <er>Pelf</er>.]</ety> <def>To steal in small
quantities, or articles of small value; to practice petty
theft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilfer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pilfer
<hw>Pil"fer</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To take by petty theft; to
filch; to steal little by little.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And not a year but <qex>pilfers</qex> as he goes⟦br⟧
Some youthful grace that age would gladly keep.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilferer</ent>⟦br⟧
